    <description><![CDATA[
# ECS Voyager

A powerful Terminal User Interface (TUI) for managing AWS ECS (Elastic Container Service) clusters, services, and tasks. Built with Rust and ratatui.

## Features

- **Interactive TUI**: Beautiful, responsive terminal interface
- **Cluster Management**: Browse and manage ECS clusters
- **Service Operations**: View, restart, and update services
- **Task Management**: Monitor tasks, view logs, and execute commands
- **CloudWatch Integration**: View logs and metrics directly in the terminal
- **ECS Exec**: Execute commands in running containers
- **Port Forwarding**: Forward local ports to container ports
- **Search & Filtering**: Powerful search with regex support
- **Metrics Visualization**: View CPU and memory metrics with ASCII charts
- **Profile & Region Switching**: Easily switch AWS profiles and regions

## Requirements

- AWS CLI configured with credentials
- For ECS Exec and Port Forwarding: [session-manager-plugin](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/systems-manager/latest/userguide/session-manager-working-with-install-plugin.html)

## Usage

Simply run `ecs-voyager` from your terminal. Use arrow keys or vim-style navigation (j/k) to navigate.

Press '?' for help.
